==English==
===Etymology 1===
From Latin [[brachiatus]], from [[brachium]] ‘arm, branch’.

====Pronunciation====
{{IPA|/ˈbrækɪət/}}

====Adjective====
{{en-adj}}
# Having [[decussate]] [[branches]].

===Etymology 2===
Back-formation from [[brachiator]].

====Pronunciation====
{{IPA|/ˈbrækɪeɪt/}}

===Verb===
